X-ray powder diffraction (XRD) patterns were recorded at room temperature using a Bruker D8 Advance diffractometer (Bruker Co., Billerica, MA, USA) equipped with a LYNXEYE position sensitive detector using Cu-K α radiation (
λ = 0 . 15418
nm
). The data were collected in Bragg–Brentano (
θ / θ
) horizontal geometry (flat reflection mode) between 10° and 70° (2 θ ) in a continuous scan using 0.03° steps 960 s/step. The data were collected under standard laboratory conditions (temperature and relative humidity).
